CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 11, 1957, pg. A12, reads: "STUNNING...FABULOUS...FASCINATING were just some of the adjectives used in connection with the annual Fashion Show given at Schenley High School by the Beauty Shop Owners and Beauticians... Right: Carmen Murphy of Detroit, guest model, shows an Opal Pritchard creation, a sheathe - beaded and sequined under a slim - Jim coat, collared with silver blue mink in over-the-head style."
TitMainTitle: Carmen Murphy wearing an Opal Pritchard sequined sheath and light colored coat with silver blue mink collar, standing on terrazzo floor in Schenley High School for annual Beauty Shop Owners fashion show
